From: Thomas Gleixner <tglx@linutronix.de>
Subject: sched: mark SCHED_HRTICK broken
Date: Wed, 28 Jan 2009 16:46:24 +0100

SCHED_HRTICK is broken and not yet fixed in mainline. WTF is it still
enabled in -rt ?

Tested-by: Carsten Emde <C.Emde@osadl.org>
Signed-off-by: Thomas Gleixner <tglx@linutronix.de>
---
 kernel/Kconfig.hz |    2 +-
 1 file changed, 1 insertion(+), 1 deletion(-)

Index: linux-2.6.26.8-rt14/kernel/Kconfig.hz
===================================================================
--- linux-2.6.26.8-rt14.orig/kernel/Kconfig.hz	2009-01-28 22:55:36.000000000 -0500
+++ linux-2.6.26.8-rt14/kernel/Kconfig.hz	2009-01-28 22:59:37.000000000 -0500
@@ -55,4 +55,4 @@ config HZ
 	default 1000 if HZ_1000
 
 config SCHED_HRTICK
-	def_bool HIGH_RES_TIMERS && X86
+	def_bool HIGH_RES_TIMERS && X86 && BROKEN
